53,http://www.armslist.com/posts/3698053,For Sale:  .300 AAC BlackOut Handi-Rifle,"s.nh, New Hampshire, United States",$ 360,"Listed On: Tuesday, November 11, 2014",Rifles,H&R                                                                                ,300 Blackout (7.62x35mm)                                                                                ,Break Open                                                                                ,Rifle,"purchased this rifle 3 months ago , has less than 30 rounds down tube , in immaculate condition (as good as new as i can tell but will leave that up to buyer), as stated above it is the Advanced Armament Corp. 300 blackout handi rifle , super compact little ranch or target rifle , has factory 5r threaded 5/8x24 and included hammer spur (offset hammer for use with optics so no fumbling around) had intended on using as a host firearm but no longer need. includes everything it came with new. Has stock pack that is included
aac specs :
300 AAC BLACKOUT - HANDI-RIFLE
Caliber:300 AAC BLACKOUT
Weight:5 lbs.
Length:16.1” Low Profile Barrel
Mount:5/8-24TPI

The H&R Handi-Rifle, made to AAC specifications and chambered in 300 AAC BLACKOUT, is a 30 caliber rifle in a very compact and lightweight package with such minimal recoil that anyone can comfortably shoot it. This durable, optics ready break action single shot rifle is ideal for the beginner and great fun for the experienced shooter. The barrel is a low profile lightweight 16.1” barrel threaded 5/8-24TPI with a 5R 1:7"" twist. The rifle accurately sends rounds down range whether feeding it heavy subsonic or high performance hunting ammunition.
